      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(webchat): recover session after stop",
        "body": "Fixes #91987.\n\n## Summary\n- Persist successful WebChat `chat.abort` requests as terminal `killed` session lifecycle before the RPC responds, including `abortedLastRun: true`, `endedAt`, and `runtimeMs`.\n- Reconcile WebChat locally after a successful Stop so the active run id/stream/tool state are cleared even if the terminal chat event is delayed or lost.\n- Add regression coverage for the stale `running` session row and local Stop recovery path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed\n- Clicking Stop during an active WebChat run no longer leaves the selected session stuck as `status: \"running\"` / `abortedLastRun: false`, and the client no longer depends on a later terminal event before it can send again.\n\nReal environment tested\n- Local macOS worktree at `/Users/andy/openclaw-91987-webchat-stop-recovery` on branch `codex/91987-webchat-stop-recovery`, Node/Vitest via the repository runner after `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/run-lifecycle.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/chat-abort.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/chat.abort-persistence.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n\nEvidence after fix\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts` now verifies a successful abort clears `chatRunId`, clears `chatStream`, and preserves visible partial text as an assistant stream fallback.\n- `src/gateway/server-methods/chat.abort-persistence.test.ts` now verifies a run-scoped RPC abort changes a temp session store row from `running` to `killed` with `abortedLastRun: true` before the handler responds.\n- All listed tests and the local changed-file check passed.\n\nObserved result after fix\n- Successful Stop terminalizes the authoritative session row and immediately frees the WebChat client to continue the same session without requiring `/reset` or a page refresh.\n\nWhat was not tested\n- I did not run a browser-driven live model/provider session; this proof uses the production gateway/UI handlers under the repository's Vitest runner and temp session-store fixtures.\n",
